      "daily_reflection": "Today, I ate for breakfast a banana. For lunch, a piece of toast with some butter and marmite. And then for dinner I had, some roast chicken which was left over from a meal I had with my family last night, some chips and some peas as well. I chose to eat those things today because it's just what, what I had at home, and I didn't have any plans to go anywhere. For the last week, I've been at home from uni, staying with my family. So, yeah, it was just whatever was in the house today. It doesn't really reflect my typical day to day food habits just because when I'm at uni, which is the majority of the time, apart from the summer, I tend to just eat a bit more because there is more available to me. I go to university in Manchester, like, very close to the center of Manchester. So there's quite a lot of there are quite a lot of food options available, so I just naturally end up eating a bit more than, when I come home because my family lives in, they live in quite a remote village with not so much to eat around. So it just it's not really reflective of my day to day food habits in that way. Although my family is very much they're very big on, like, not wasting food and using up what we have. So, like, my our our dinner today was just made up of things that, like, needed eating, like the chicken. And then, the peas and the chips were like we were doing kind of a a big, like, freezer audit. So I did pick up that family that, sorry, that habit from my family, to use things up, but, it doesn't really reflect my day to day eating habits just because I normally do eat more when I'm at uni. And I also am a lot more active when I'm at uni, so I feel like I need to eat more."
